ox. ¾ in.)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"9 oz whole milk, plus extra to glaze"}],"nutrition":["per 1 pieces","958 kJ \/ 229 kcal","7 g","26 g","11 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["This recipes uses strong or mature\/aged cheddar. For children, use medium or mild cheddar.","When using a biscuit cutter, do not twist it or your biscuits will rise unevenly. Just press straight down and lift straight up, shaking cutter to loosen dough if necessary.","Best eaten the same day they're made, or freeze on day of baking once completely cooled.","Biscuit dough can become tough if handled too much or if overmixed so use a light hand and work swiftly."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","20m","14 pieces"]}